{"key":"processedPost-5103106","value":{"id":5103106,"first":5101930,"last":7838199,"when":1135482041,"utime":"12/25/05 05:40 AM","content":"You want hydrated lime because it's water soluable and goes to work immediately.  Garden lime is intended to break down over several months during the outdoor growing season and will be useless during the three to four week life of a casing layer.<br /><br />Use hydrated lime at the rate of 5% by volume of the amount of peat in the casing.  In other words, for 20 pints of peat, use 1 pint of hydrated lime.  Don't count the vermiculite when figuring how much lime to use.<br />RR","title":"Re: how much lime?"}}